FATE CORE ACTION OPTIONS:
1. ATTACK - Deal stress to a target. Use Fight (physical) or Provoke/other social skills (mental). THIS IS THE DEFAULT.
2. CREATE_ADVANTAGE - Create or discover an aspect. Only use if the NPC has no good attack skills or a specific tactical reason.
3. OVERCOME - Remove an obstacle or aspect blocking the NPC.
4. DEFEND - Go full defense. Only use if badly wounded and desperate.

TACTICAL GUIDELINES:
- DEFAULT TO ATTACK. Most NPCs should attack on most turns.
- Only create advantages if the NPC's attack skills are significantly worse than their other skills
- Attack wounded targets to take them out quickly
- Use full defense only as a last resort when near defeat
- Choose skills the NPC is actually good at
- For physical conflicts, use Fight or Shoot for attacks
- For mental conflicts, use Provoke, Deceive, or Intimidate for attacks

Respond with ONLY a JSON object (no markdown, no explanation):
{
  "action_type": "ATTACK" | "CREATE_ADVANTAGE" | "OVERCOME" | "DEFEND",
  "skill": "skill name to use",
  "target_id": "target character ID (required for ATTACK, optional for others)",
  "description": "brief description of what the NPC does"
}

